gomodel:SYNGO_2861  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Ultrastructural localization of endogenous Rab5 in CA1 neurons of rat hippocampus.\"\n- \" Most synaptic Rab5 immunolabeling was found in the postsynaptic terminal (~75%; Figure 1A, arrows; Figure 1B, \"POST\"). Furthermore, we found that postsynaptic Rab5 labeling was predominantly located outside of the postsynaptic density (PSD) on lateral extrasynaptic membranes (Figure 1B, \"Memb.\"), roughly 100-300 nm away from the edge of the PSD (Figure 1C). This localization fits well with \"endocytic hotspots\" previously described lateral to the PSD (Blanpied et al., 2002; Petralia et al., 2003; Racz et al., 2004).\"\n\nNote: the imaging data by itself does not resolve the endocytic zone. The rest of the paper shows a role of Rab5 in AMPAR endocytosis and the localization lateral of the PSD is suggestive of the postsynaptic endocytic zone.. Experimental description: - \"Ultrastructural localization of endogenous Rab5 in CA1 neurons of rat hippocampus.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-20" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2861" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

